  "response": "As of the latest data available (2023), the average number of followers per user on Instagram is **estimated to be around 150 to 200 followers**. However, this average can vary significantly depending on factors such as:\n\n1. **User Activity**: Highly active users or influencers tend to have significantly more followers than casual users.\n2. **Account Type**: Business accounts, creators, or public figures often have more followers than personal or private accounts.\n3. **Time on Platform**: Long-time users typically accumulate more followers than new users.\n4. **Geographic Location**: Users in certain regions or countries may have more or fewer followers based on Instagram's popularity and usage patterns in those areas.\n\nIt's worth noting that follower counts are highly skewed, with a small percentage of users (e.g., celebrities and influencers) having millions of followers, while the majority of users have much smaller follower counts. If you\u2019re looking for more precise or updated data, you may need to refer to Instagram's official reports or third-party analytics tools.",
